Author: AndrewK#3947
Content: Yes. Ease of use & holding/buying is a HUGE factor. But understand that the majority of the adoption and value of crypto today doesn't come from actual usage. Its from SPECULATION. You, me, everyone here is speculating on a future price increase. Everyone in crypto is. But why do people speculate? Because they believe in future adoption and future real utility which comes features like SPV, and payment integrations, etc., but ultimately comes down to the tech. These other lower tier privacy shitcoins can have as many exchange listing and merchant support as they want, but noone gives a shit because they have no real utility/privacy edge over Monero or Zcash. Take this from someone with a profession institutional background in crypto investing (not that that means anything with all these underperforming funds lol)

Author: AndrewK#3947
Content: People hate the action of speculating, but at the end of the day, the price increase that resulted from the speculation was the most important piece for bitcoin's rise because it gave it attention & liquidity which makes it more pertinent for non-retail players. The same is true for any other crypto.
